  "texts": [
    "(7)Encoder freezing strategy.",
    "To leverage pretrained representations efficiently, we keep all encoders (DINOv3, SigLIP, T5) frozen throughout training and trains only the fusion layer and decoder, following [20].",
    "TraceGen learns a unified policy in 3D trace space, predicting future scene-level trajectories that are embodiment-agnostic.",
    "To execute on a specific robot, these traces must be \"translated\" into the robot's action space via a lightweight warm-up.",
    "We evaluate two lightweight regimes that differ only in the source of supervision for warm-up (For both warm-up regimes, we do not cherry-pick demonstrations."
  ],
